BankAmerica Corp is seeking a buyerfor its branch in Asuncion, Paraguay, a spokesman in Miami forthe bank holding company said.    "We are in ongoing negotiations for the sale of ourParaguay operations," the spokesman said. He declined to namethe possible buyer.    A sale of the Paraguayan operations, which employ about 80people, would be consistent with Bank of America's strategy ofconcentrating its international efforts on wholesale banking,he added. The bank has sold operations in a number of countriesrecently, including Italy and Sri Lanka. Reuter&#3;